Tonight —
Okay lol I’m done but you get the jazz. No funny stuff. Tho. Just my experience and my thoughts… heheh.

I’m joking. I’d like that cash tho you see what I’m sayin?  Bruh what a fricken dream tho damn. Doing stuff you love while making money is hard af No fucking cap… Them celebs be real fancy… EXCEPT THE DAMN PAPARAZZI BECAUSE I WOULD HATE THAT AT SO MUCH.

I also just make music for fun, but possibly might look for some 💵 in the future. Not as a job, but a side hustle. If things go real high, I’m gonna go straight to the dumpster because I sure as heck do not want to be a musician known for being canceled about something…
I’m just really happy that I was able to finally reach 300. “My dream follower count” LMAO 😭😭 I was desperate, not really. I just hope ya’ll get what I’m saying.

Not all experiences is the same, this is just MY POINT OF VIEW and how I was able to surpass my long years of “agony and expressionism” as artists say. This 300 followers stuff on SoundCloud isn’t much for a lot of other people out there, but it’s a big mile stone for me.

This ain’t the case for ppl with 5000+ followers or celebrities tho plz don’t spam them. Cause they probably not gonna see you cause they message a lot of ppl or they block you for spamming or they just ignore you. :[ sorry for the cold hard truth.

You gotta speak up and say “hi, I really like ‘your song’, I hope you’ll like my song.” And surly they will answer you. I don’t get 100+ messages a day (and I don’t wanna) but I get 1 in a month saying “hi, see my song plz”, and I literally do the same for them. 🤷🏻‍♀️

It’s all networking and saying hi to eachother and similar to “moots” on twitter, ya know. Also commenting on other people’s music (usually positive but critiquing only when they ask) is a real 👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻 like please do that more often????? Uhhhh we need it?

Some these folks are middle aged dude!!! Like they know more than me in music!!!! They been there for so long, before I’ve been born!!! Like, the fuck??! 
Like they be really friendly and fun people too!!

Also you have to try to find your way into a social network in SoundCloud. There will be a group of people that know eachother through SoundCloud, I kid you not. Ambient makers, techno, trance, all that good stuff. They be remixing each others stuff, ya know, bla bla bla.

People keep asking me “How you get real follower on SoundCloud????”
I say this.
It takes three to five years to actually get to 50 followers. Then another 2 for more. It’s a harsh waiting game. And you try to get out of bot situations. It’s ugly.
